setUpdateRange

public void setUpdateRange(String updateRange)
Explicitly sets the update range as a string value. No checking is done for correctness. The "bytes=" portion of the header should be omitted.

Parameters:
updateRange - the updateRange to set (e.g. "100-199"). See RFC 2616, section 14.35.1 for more information on byte ranges.
